NS-CHRONICLE-000 — CHARTER (Daily Continuity + Productivity)

1) Mission

Create a lightweight, high-signal daily continuity system that captures what you planned, what you actually did, why it mattered, and what carries forward—so you can “resume instantly” each morning.

2) Problem statement

High-context work (Northfield Solidarity engines/projects) creates cognitive load. Without a consistent daily record, momentum and continuity degrade across sleep cycles, interruptions, and context switching.

3) Scope

In scope

A twice-daily routine:

Morning Brief (plan + priorities + risks)

Evening Debrief (what happened + outcomes + carryovers)

XML-first output so it can be:

stored, diffed, indexed, and ingested into your graph systems (GGE / DRE / quickscope)

Minimal friction: 3–10 minutes AM, 5–12 minutes PM.

Out of scope (for now)

Full task management replacement

Calendar automation (can be integrated later)

4) Core principles

First-person truth: written from your perspective (I did / I decided / I learned).

Outcome over activity: track deliverables and decisions, not just effort.

Carryover clarity: every open loop becomes a named carryover or is explicitly dropped.

Evidence linkage: attach doc IDs, PRs, tickets, runbooks, or notes where possible.

5) Interfaces with Northfield Solidarity

GGE: decisions, policies, governance changes

DRE: research threads and findings to map into the graph

quickscope (Intervention): state snapshots + next state transitions

NS-LUM: ops/observability work and incidents (high-level summary)

6) Deliverables

Standard XML schemas:

MorningBrief

EveningDebrief

Daily archive convention: one file per day per brief/debrief

Optional weekly synthesis later (rollups)

7) Success metrics

“Time-to-context” each morning ≤ 5 minutes

Fewer dropped threads (carryover completion rate rises)

Clear decision log continuity across NS projects

NS-CHRONICLE-001 — Daily XML Templates

A) Morning Brief XML (copy/paste)

<MorningBrief>
  <Meta>
    <Date>YYYY-MM-DD</Date>
    <Timezone>America/New_York</Timezone>
    <Author>John</Author>
    <Version>1.0</Version>
  </Meta>

  <Context>
    <OneSentenceIntent>I want today to be about ...</OneSentenceIntent>
    <ContinuityFromYesterday>
      <Carryovers>
        <Item>
          <Title></Title>
          <WhyItMatters></WhyItMatters>
          <NextAction></NextAction>
          <Blocker></Blocker>
          <Link></Link>
        </Item>
      </Carryovers>
    </ContinuityFromYesterday>
  </Context>

  <TodayPlan>
    <TopPriorities>
      <Priority>
        <Title></Title>
        <OutcomeDefinition>By end of day, success looks like ...</OutcomeDefinition>
        <TimeBoxMinutes></TimeBoxMinutes>
        <Dependencies></Dependencies>
        <Risk></Risk>
        <Link></Link>
      </Priority>
    </TopPriorities>

    <SecondaryGoals>
      <Goal>
        <Title></Title>
        <OutcomeDefinition></OutcomeDefinition>
      </Goal>
    </SecondaryGoals>

    <DecisionQueue>
      <Decision>
        <Question></Question>
        <Options></Options>
        <Lean></Lean>
      </Decision>
    </DecisionQueue>

    <Constraints>
      <Constraint>Meetings, travel, energy limits, deadlines...</Constraint>
    </Constraints>

    <FocusRules>
      <Rule>What I will NOT do today</Rule>
      <Rule>Distraction kill-switch (e.g., block X, ignore Y)</Rule>
    </FocusRules>
  </TodayPlan>

  <Mindset>
    <EnergyLevel>low|medium|high</EnergyLevel>
    <MainThreatToMomentum></MainThreatToMomentum>
    <OneCommitment>I commit to ...</OneCommitment>
  </Mindset>
</MorningBrief>

B) Evening Debrief XML (copy/paste)

<EveningDebrief>
  <Meta>
    <Date>YYYY-MM-DD</Date>
    <Timezone>America/New_York</Timezone>
    <Author>John</Author>
    <Version>1.0</Version>
  </Meta>

  <Summary>
    <OneParagraphFromMyPerspective>
      Today I...
    </OneParagraphFromMyPerspective>
    <Score>
      <Outcome>0-10</Outcome>
      <Focus>0-10</Focus>
      <Energy>0-10</Energy>
    </Score>
  </Summary>

  <WhatIShipped>
    <Item>
      <Title></Title>
      <Type>doc|code|decision|infra|research|ops</Type>
      <Impact></Impact>
      <Link></Link>
    </Item>
  </WhatIShipped>

  <WhatIWorkedOn>
    <WorkBlock>
      <Project>NS-____</Project>
      <WhatIDid></WhatIDid>
      <Result></Result>
      <TimeSpentMinutes></TimeSpentMinutes>
      <Links></Links>
    </WorkBlock>
  </WhatIWorkedOn>

  <Decisions>
    <Decision>
      <Title></Title>
      <Context></Context>
      <Choice></Choice>
      <Rationale></Rationale>
      <Consequences></Consequences>
      <Link></Link>
    </Decision>
  </Decisions>

  <Learnings>
    <Learning>
      <WhatILearned></WhatILearned>
      <HowItChangesTomorrow></HowItChangesTomorrow>
    </Learning>
  </Learnings>

  <Problems>
    <Problem>
      <WhatWentWrong></WhatWentWrong>
      <RootCauseHypothesis></RootCauseHypothesis>
      <FixNextTime></FixNextTime>
    </Problem>
  </Problems>

  <Continuity>
    <Carryovers>
      <Item>
        <Title></Title>
        <NextAction></NextAction>
        <Priority>high|medium|low</Priority>
        <Blocker></Blocker>
        <Link></Link>
      </Item>
    </Carryovers>

    <TomorrowSeed>
      <Top3Candidates>
        <Candidate>
          <Title></Title>
          <Why></Why>
        </Candidate>
      </Top3Candidates>
    </TomorrowSeed>
  </Continuity>

  <Closeout>
    <GratitudeOrWin></GratitudeOrWin>
    <ShutdownPhrase>Done for today.</ShutdownPhrase>
  </Closeout>
</EveningDebrief>

NS-CHRONICLE-002 — “Ask ChatGPT” Prompts (so you always get XML)

Morning prompt

Generate a MorningBrief in the NS-CHRONICLE XML format. Write in first-person (“I…”). Use my carryovers and current priorities from this chat. If info is missing, leave fields empty rather than inventing.

Evening prompt

Generate an EveningDebrief in the NS-CHRONICLE XML format. Write in first-person (“I…”). Summarize what I worked on today based on this chat, including what I shipped, decisions I made, and carryovers. If unsure, mark the field as <Uncertain>true</Uncertain> inside the relevant item.

